- core:
    - ensure only one root node exists
    - don't let loose tag destroy structure when now parent
      allows it, actions in this case could be:
      - find container for a parent
    - merge tags of which only one is allowed (like head for html)
    - move parsing stuff to a parser class
	- create unit tests for parser
	- treat cdata as text (cdata should extend text?)
    - document structure:
	- add isKnownEntity to doc structure interface and use it
	  for text tokens
	- smarter container rules for |, + and ?
	- handle #implied, #required and cdata, nmtoken and id
	  attributes
    - include xhtml-1.0 document structure object
    - optional case insensitive tags (using ds version)
    - handle empty tags
    - passes:
	- tokenize
	- hierarchy
	- tree balansing
	    - merge too many tags
	    - move lost tags
- frontends:
    - commandline:
	--comment-illegal-code
	--discard-comments
	--discard-special
	--discard-decl
	--transform-cdata
    - web xhtmlizer:
	validate, report and deliver bodyshopped version
